These creatures have flat faces, broad noses, pointed ears, wide mouths, and small, sharp fangs. Most consider them to be little more than a nuisance, but unchecked they can despoil civilized areas.

Orcs are a species of aggressive mammalian carnivores that band together in tribes and survive by hunting and raiding. Orcs believe that in order to survive they must expand their territory, and so they are constantly involved in wars against many enemies: humans, elves, dwarves, goblins, and other orc tribes.

This is a beastman, a variety of gnoll colloquially termed so in local dialect for their unusually sharp intellect. They stand around seven and a half feet, heavily built with dark fur. The more dominant members of the tribe tend to display fur of a pure black. As gnolls, they invariably hold a malicious, sadistic streak of blood-lust and cruelty.

Being bred into harsh climes, these trolls are much sturdier than their lower altitude kin.  They hold a particular hatred for dwarves as these races often find themselves battling over territory.

Dogma of Maglubiyet: Maglubiyet revels in conflict and destruction and constantly pushes his followers to wage war, particularly against dwarves and gnomes. He encourages goblins to increase their numbers in order to overrun their enemies. As a paranoid god he is prone to destroy lesser goblin deities when he suspects treachery or he thinks they are becoming too powerful.
